description.narrative: In 2019 UNICEF provided technical expertise to Government to reform social protection system and supported intersectoral consultation on the institutional integration resulting in a draft decree for the establishment of the state body on social protection. UNICEF successfully led efforts to mobilize resources for the UN Joint Programme on Social Protection to support the Government in establishing the single state body for social protection in 2020-2021. Government's capacity in applying integrated approaches in social protection was also strengthened through piloting single registry, individual capacity development on universal child benefits and utilizing existing mechanisms for humanitarian cash transfers. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
